column1:
Skip content section

Let's Work Together

Freshworks makes it easy for IT, Customer Service, Sales, Marketing and HR to be more human, more open, and more focused on the things people love. Its intuitive and easy-to-use solutions feel like they were designed to make people’s work lives easier – because they were.
Right now, Freshworks is looking for brilliant, passionate people who are a joy to work with, in locations all over the world. If you think you might be one of them,&nbsp
column2:
let’s work together.

Diversity, Equity, Inclusion, Kudumba.

At Freshworks, we believe diversity powers innovation—because great ideas can and do come from everyone, everywhere. That’s why we encourage people from all backgrounds—particularly historically underrepresented and marginalized ones—to join our Kudumba. It’s our own word, derived from the Tamil word for “family,” and it describes Freshworks perfectly. This is an eclectic, diverse family of people who believe a better, fresher way to work starts with a better, fresher place to work.
column3: We have always taken pride in being a company that is loved by its employees, customers, and stakeholders—in that order. It’s simple — happy, fulfilled employees do better, more innovative work.
column4: That’s why we do everything we can to create a workplace where everyone can bring their true selves to work, feel comfortable speaking out, take risks, and feel they’re an integral part of the Freshworks Kudumba.&nbsp
column5: We were born out of frustration with the impersonal, one-size-fits-all way companies treat people.
column6: We believe we can do better. And we believe better starts with us.&nbsp
column7: If that sounds like a Kudumba you’d like to be a part of,
column8:
let’s work together.

column1: <meta property=""og:description"" content=""Optimal Dynamics is on a mission to automate and optimize the logistics industry through the use of advanced analytics. We are based on more than three decades of R&amp
column3: D at Princeton University and represent the most sophisticated technology ever developed for the logistics industry. Optimal Dynamics is a high-growth early-stage company with ~70 employees (but changing very quickly!) and $56M in funding.

column1: We are a team of bright, kind, and solution-oriented people focused on creating value for our customers. We can solve problems individually, but understand that the best solutions are found when the team brainstorms ideas together. We are excited about balancing the need to deploy new solutions quickly and designing solutions that are secured, reliable, maintainable and scalable for the long run.
